# 3. Operator rules used consistently

The following operator values are fixed for all demonstrations in this paper.

```text
q  = strong external initiation / process start / flow start
p  = operational initiation / procedure-init / subprocedure-start
f  = material/preparatory/variant initiation
o  = process field / node / base field
a  = transition / to / toward / into
d  = transformation / processing
y  = boundary / closure / finalization
e  = grade / intensity / internal differentiation
i  = phase marker / sequence marker
n  = phase boundary / stage endpoint
l  = local carrier / locality
r  = relation / output direction
m  = terminal mass / base / residue
k  = stabilization / fixation / left-binding connector
t  = transfer / routing
s  = regulated/status marker
h  = activation / execution / internal activation binder
ch = active coupled frame
sh = activated regulation/status
cth = active coupled transfer
ckh = active coupled stabilization
cph = active coupled procedure/separation
cfh = active coupled variant/preparation
```

Closure and target forms:

```text
dy    = transformation + closure
daiin = transformation toward second phase
dar   = transformation toward output/relation
dol   = transformation into local carrier
dam   = transformation toward terminal base/mass
ar    = toward output/relation
ol    = local carrier field
ot    = transfer field
ok    = stabilized/fixed field
op    = procedure/extraction field
```

These values may not be redefined during the translation of a folio.

